Here's a definition of the `FloatWithUnits` struct with a `show` method:

```rust
struct FloatWithUnits {
    value: f64,
    unit: String,
}

impl ToString for FloatWithUnits {
    fn to_string(&self) -> String {
        format!("{} {}", self.value, self.unit)
    }
}
```

In this example, we are implementing the `ToString` trait for the `FloatWithUnits` struct. The `to_string()` function will be called when you use the `show` method on an instance of the struct. It formats the value and unit fields with a space in between.
